comment: [Incidental or immaterial] Whiteside (MIA) grabs Horford's (BOS) jersey.
Richardson (MIA) makes incidental contact with Thomas (BOS) that does not affect his SQBR.
Correctly called 24 second violation.
Crowder (BOS) jumps from point A to point B into Johnson (MIA) and the contact to the body affects his jump shot attempt.
RO SLA shows Dragic (MIA) clamp Smart's (BOS) arm and affect his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Dragic (MIA) makes marginal contact with Smart (BOS) that does not affect his SQBR.
Whiteside (MIA) obtains a legal guarding position and jumps vertically as he contests Thomas' (BOS) driving shot attempt.
Crowder (BOS) makes contact to Johnson's (BOS) head that affects his driving shot attempt.
Whiteside (MIA) makes contact to Thomas' (BOS) arm that affects his driving shot attempt.
Bradley (BOS) legally contests Johnson's (MIA) jump shot attempt. Any "high five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Dragic (MIA) dislodges Smart (BOS), affecting his ability to retrieve the rebound.

After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor of a goaltending violation on Whiteside (MIA) stands.
Horford (BOS) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Johnson (BOS) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Whiteside (MIA) makes incidental contact with Smart (BOS) during rebounding.
Smart (BOS) makes contact with the ball as Whiteside (MIA) gathers the rebound.
Johnson (MIA) makes incidental contact with Horford (BOS) during the inbound.
McGruder (MIA) commits a take foul on Crowder (BOS).
Horford (BOS) makes marginal contact with Johnson (MIA) that does not affect his SQBR.
Horford (BOS) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Johnson (MIA) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Whiteside (MIA) and Crowder (BOS) briefly engage and separate off ball.
Smart (BOS) legally contests Johnson's (MIA) jump shot attempt.
